These are too slow.

Solutions:

### Solution 1:  change `conmon` to open log file in non-blocking mode:

in `src/ctr_logging.c`

```diff
diff --git b/src/ctr_logging.c a/src/ctr_logging.c
index 139cb6a..fd530d6 100644
--- b/src/ctr_logging.c
+++ a/src/ctr_logging.c
@@ -105,7 +105,7 @@ void configure_log_drivers(gchar **log_drivers, int64_t log_size_max_, char *cuu
        }
        if (use_k8s_logging) {
                /* Open the log path file. */
-               k8s_log_fd = open(k8s_log_path, O_WRONLY | O_APPEND | O_CREAT | O_CLOEXEC, 0600);
+               k8s_log_fd = open(k8s_log_path, O_WRONLY | O_NONBLOCK | O_APPEND | O_CREAT | O_CLOEXEC, 0600);
                if (k8s_log_fd < 0)
                        pexit("Failed to open log file");
```

in above situation ( log file is a named pipe and there's no reader currently),  conmon will failed very fast with an error "Failed to open log file", there is no stucking.

Result: I have compiled the code and tested it, this works.

### Solution 2

Hack `nomad-driver-podman` to open a non-blocking reader just before it try to start a exited container.

Result: I have compiled the code and tested it, this works.
